  "joke": "Suzy Izzard: Imagine the U.S. military lurking in the shadows like a superhero who's run out of good ideas—weeks-long operations in Iran, they say, while Iran is probably just over there like, \"Can someone hand me a sandwich? I’m about to collapse here!” And meanwhile, Canada’s just standing on the sidelines, arms crossed, like that aunt at a family barbecue, muttering something about “no regime change till I see real commitment, dear.” And what’s China up to? Xi Jinping’s elite are disappearing faster than my will to do cardio when I see a donut! It’s all so absurd—if this were a reality TV show, we’d be a blend of “Survivor,” “The Bachelor,” and “Whose Line Is It Anyway?” with the world basically shouting, “Next contestant, please!” while sporting a charm bracelet of historical blunders that jingles every time someone mentions diplomacy!",
